{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Dedicated Stripe Service Layer\n      Create a services/stripe/ module that encapsulates all Stripe interactions. Server actions and API routes call into the service layer.\n      \n        Flow:\n        Server Action → StripeService.createCheckoutSession() → Stripe API\n        Webhook API Route → StripeService.handleEvent() → DB update\n      \n      \n        Pros\n          All Stripe logic in one place\n          Easier to test Stripe interactions in isolation\n        \n        Cons\n          New pattern not used elsewhere in codebase\n          Extra abstraction layer for ~3-4 Stripe calls\n          YAGNI — premature for this phase's scope","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1775457575067}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Server Actions + API Routes (Recommended)\n      Keep the existing pattern. Server actions for mutations (create checkout session, handle onboarding), API route for the webhook endpoint. Stripe logic in a shared lib/stripe.ts helper.\n      \n        Flow:\n        Member Dashboard → \"Pay Now\" → Server Action creates Checkout Session → Redirect to Stripe → Stripe sends webhook → API Route updates transaction\n      \n      \n        Pros\n          Matches existing codebase patterns (server actions everywhere)\n          Type-safe end-to-end with Drizzle\n          Webhook is naturally an API route (not a server action)\n          Minimal new abstractions\n        \n        Cons\n          Stripe logic split between actions/ and api/ directories","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1775457579271}
